        "content": "Q1: Which is the largest national park in India?\n• Hemis National Park, Ladakh, is the largest national park in India.\n\nQ2: Which is the first national park established in India?\n• Jim Corbett National Park, Uttarakhand, was the first national park in India.\n\nQ3: Which sanctuary is famous for the great Indian bustard?\n• Rollapadu Wildlife Sanctuary, Andhra Pradesh, is known for the great Indian bustard.\n\nQ4: Which sanctuary is famous for the Asiatic lion?\n• Gir National Park, Gujarat, is home to the Asiatic lion.\n\nQ5: Which sanctuary is known for elephants in Kerala?\n• Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary, Kerala, is famous for elephants.\n\nQ6: Which is India’s tiger capital?\n• Madhya Pradesh, specifically Kanha and Bandhavgarh National Parks, is considered India’s tiger capital.\n\nQ7: Which sanctuary is important for migratory birds in Tamil Nadu?\n• Vedanthangal Bird Sanctuary is famous for migratory birds.\n\nQ8: Which sanctuary is famous for blackbucks in Punjab?\n• Abohar Wildlife Sanctuary is known for blackbucks.\n\nQ9: Which national park is a UNESCO World Heritage Site?\n• Great Himalayan National Park, Himachal Pradesh, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.\n\nQ10: Which sanctuary protects marine biodiversity in India?\n• Gulf of Mannar Marine National Park, Tamil Nadu, protects marine biodiversity.\n\nQ11: Which sanctuary is famous for snow leopards?\n• Hemis National Park, Ladakh, and Pin Valley National Park, Himachal Pradesh, are known for snow leopards.\n\nQ12: How many national parks are there in India?\n• As of 2025, there are 106 national parks in India.\n\nQ13: How many wildlife sanctuaries are there in India?\n• As of 2025, there are 566 wildlife sanctuaries in India.\n\nQ14: Which sanctuary is famous for wetland and migratory birds in Delhi?\n• Asola Bhatti Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\nQ15: Which sanctuary is known for black panthers in Karnataka?\n• Dandeli Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\nQ16: Which sanctuary protects the Hangul deer?\n• Dachigam National Park, Jammu & Kashmir.\n\nQ17: Which sanctuary is famous for marine turtles?\n• Bhitarkanika Wildlife Sanctuary, Odisha.\n\nQ18: Which sanctuary is famous for gharials?\n• National Chambal Sanctuary, Uttar Pradesh/Madhya Pradesh/Rajasthan.\n\nQ19: Which sanctuary is known for hornbills?\n• Dandeli Wildlife Sanctuary, Karnataka.\n\nQ20: Which sanctuary protects the Indian one-horned rhinoceros?\n• Kaziranga National Park, Assam.\n\nQ21: Which sanctuary is known for migratory birds in Maharashtra?\n• Nandur Madhameshwar Bird Sanctuary.\n\nQ22: Which sanctuary is famous for tigers in Karnataka?\n• Bandipur and Nagarhole National Parks.\n\nQ23: Which sanctuary is famous for tigers and elephants in Kerala?\n• Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\nQ24: Which sanctuary is known for snowcapped Himalayan fauna?\n• Great Himalayan National Park, Himachal Pradesh.\n\nQ25: Which sanctuary is famous for marine life and coral reefs in India?\n• Gulf of Mannar Marine National Park, Tamil Nadu.\n\nQ26: Which sanctuary is important for wetland conservation in Haryana?\n• Bhindawas Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\nQ27: Which sanctuary protects the Himalayan ibex?\n• Pin Valley National Park, Himachal Pradesh.\n\nQ28: Which sanctuary is famous for migratory flamingos?\n• Sewri Mudflats, Maharashtra.\n\nQ29: Which sanctuary is a habitat for brown bear in Jammu & Kashmir?\n• Overa-Aru Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\nQ30: Which sanctuary is famous for tigers in Madhya Pradesh?\n• Kanha and Bandhavgarh National Parks.\n\nQ31: Which sanctuary is famous for elephants and gaurs in Tamil Nadu?\n• Sathyamangalam Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\n"
